"footnotes":[
[
"Lynch-related tumors include colorectal, endometrial, gastric, ovarian, pancreatic, ureter and renal pelvis, biliary tract, brain, and small bowel cancer. Also included are sebaceous gland adenomas and keratocanthomas in Muir-Torre syndrome."
],
[
"CRC = colorectal cancer; MSI = microsatellite instability."
],
[
{
"type":"tag",
"tagName":"sup",
"attrs":{
},
"children":[
"a"
]
},
"Tumors should be tested for MSI, or genetic testing may be considered if criteria are met."
],
[
{
"type":"tag",
"tagName":"sup",
"attrs":{
},
"children":[
"b"
]
},
"MSI-high–like histologic features include presence of tumor infiltrating lymphocytes, Crohn-like lymphocytic reaction, mucinous or signet-ring differentiation, and medullary growth pattern."
]
]
